title: Exilryssar misstänkt förgiftade i Tyskland
cleaned_sentences: Tt Published The German police have launched a preliminary investigation into suspected poisoning since two exile cries became ill, reports Die Welt.
The two women attended a conference with Putin critic Michail Chodorkovsky in Berlin at the end of April.
One sought help for his problems at the Berlin Hospital Charité.
One of them is Natalia Arno from the Free Russia Foundation based in the United States.
On her Facebook page, she testifies to strange symptoms and acute pain.
Two weeks later she still had numbness, but states that she otherwise feels good.
